         <abstract><p>The <foreign xml:lang="gez">Fǝtḥa nagaśt</foreign> is a book of law which was in use in Ethiopia from the <date>16th century</date> and was still referenced to in the Penal and Civil Codes of 1930, 1957 and 1960.</p>
            <p>The date of its translation from the Arabic <ref target="#t2arabic"/> by <persName role="translator" ref="PRS7834PetrosA"/> is debated, possibly it was translated the <date>16th century</date>.</p>
